***
Files from the various samples are distinguished by a tag: signal_EJ, bkg_Zjets_q, bkg_Zjets_g, bkg_ZZ, bkg_HZ_SM
'''
If they contain:
_JES : sample with Jet Energy Scale lower by 4%
_etrk : sample with lowered track reconstruction efficiency
_eb : sample with lowered b-tagging efficiency
_xsec : systematic with lowered background production
'''
Two series of 1D plots were made:
*.pdf : stack of backgrounds + overlapped signal
*_stack.pdf : stack of backgrounds and signal
'''
If they contain:
_sample0 : signal
_sample1 : bkg_HZ_SM
_sample2 : bkg_ZZ
_sample3 : bkg_Zjets_g
_sample4 : bkg_Zjets_q
area_ : produced by MergeHistosArea.C, Signal area = sum of bkgs areas
CL_ : produced by Chi2_MergeHistos.C, Chi2 vs xsec_signal
sysCL_ : produced by Chi2_MergeHistos.C, Chi2 vs xsec_signal, with systematics
***

